Date:  9/9/1933
Source:  Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page:  15
Edition:
Quote:  Idiomatic use of `as' to introduce a simile. ... Two may possibly be Canterbury expressions (at least, I never heard them outside the province): (1) As rough as a bag. (2) As rough as a pig's breakfast.
Notes:  Acland Glossary

